<ol class="blogroll wp-dark-mode-bg-image">
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-55812" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://andphilosophy.com/2025/12/02/solving-the-puzzle-of-cheating-in-video-games/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">What counts as cheating in video games? What about in single-player video games?</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; Charles Joshua Horn explores these questions</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-55807" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://philosophyofbrains.com/category/books/kirchhoff-the-idealized-mind" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">“Models of the mind and brain [in cognitive science] make use of idealized terms that have no counterpart in reality… Still [they’re] consistent with a version of scientific realism.”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; a symposium on Michael Kirchhoff’s &#8220;The Idealized Mind&#8221; (at Brains)</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-55804" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://www.pbs.org/newshour/show/how-artificial-intelligence-is-reshaping-college-for-students-and-professors" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">“I have lost the very best tool that I have to see if I am being effective in my capacity as an instructor”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; Megan Fritts is one of several professors interviewed by PBS Newshour for its report on the effects of AI on academia</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-55803" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://theconversation.com/its-wanting-to-know-that-makes-us-matter-how-tom-stoppard-made-us-all-philosophers-270952" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">The philosophy in Tom Stoppard’s plays</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; an appreciation of the playwright, who died on November 29th</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-55735" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://openquestionsblog.substack.com/p/is-affirmative-action-in-faculty" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">A look at the various arguments for affirmative action in academic hiring</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; by Victor Kumar, who concludes that &#8220;If we’re serious about diversity, we should treat hiring-stage affirmative action as a secondary tool and devote most of our energy to fixing the academic pipeline&#8221;</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-55708" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://blog.apaonline.org/2025/11/25/2021-pacific-division-dewey-lecture-philosophy-and-me/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">“I was twenty-five, young enough to be severely disillusioned by the limits I had encountered [in grad school]… I was also nostalgic for my life outside of academia, which I had never fully experienced. So I turned the Barnard offer down and left philosophy…”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; Naomi Zack&#8217;s 2021 Dewey Lecture</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-55706" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://anotherpanacea.substack.com/p/hannah-arendt-judging-ai-experiment?" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">“Can an AI write Hannah Arendt’s unfinished book?”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; Joshua Miller discusses the very idea of it, an attempt he made at it, what it says about current scholarship, and what a proper go at it would be like</span></li>
</ol>
